· But, ministrant on clamorous battle-plains‚ Sated my spirit with a strange delight.

And foul'd the lustre of untarnish'd act,

And 'summon’d me from conquest to despair. Long 'years I crept through shame unmersted, Humbled in peace, all glorious in war,—

And mighty only on the battle-field.

At last, when all barbarian multitudes

Rallied upon the Eastern capital,

Justinian call'd me forth from obloquy‚
